		"description": "<p>This weapon can only be used outdoors in sunny conditions, or in places with a similarly bright source of unobstructed light (such as can be found on some other planes or generated by certain magical sources such as the daylight or sunbeam spell). &nbsp;If the source powering it counts as sunlight, so do attacks with the ray. As an action, you may create a beam of focused light 60 ft. long and 5 ft wide. &nbsp;Creatures in the area must make a Constitution saving throw with a DC of 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier. &nbsp;On a failed save they take 6d8 radiant damage, and on a successful save they take half. &nbsp;The ray cannot move and fire in the same round, as it must be recalibrated to refocus the light.</p>",
